==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hodograph
<hw>Hod"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.<?/ path +
<ets>graph</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>A curve described by
the moving extremity of a line the other end of which is fixed, this
line being constantly parallel to the direction of motion of, and having
its length constantly proportional to the velocity of, a point moving in
any path; -used in investigations respecting central forces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hodometer</ent>⟦br⟧
